SIMPLE: occurrence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Occurrence
<hw>Oc*cur"rence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>occurrence</ets>. See <er>Occur</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
coming or happening; <as>as, the <ex>occurrence</ex> of a railway
collision</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Voyages detain the mind by the perpetual <qex>occurrence</qex> and
expectation of something new.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any event or incident; esp., one which happens
without being designed or expected; <as>as, an unusual
<ex>occurrence</ex>, or the ordinary <ex>occurrences</ex> of
life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the <qex>occurrence</qex> of my fortune.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Event</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occurrent</ent>⟦br⟧
